This #WorldEnvironmentDay, meet Vandana Vijay, founder and CEO of Offbeat Tracks, an experiential travel company that promotes experiential and sustainable travel across the Himalayas. They work with rural communities to encourage homestay based travel with a focus on rural micro entrepreneurship and skill development. 
All of their projects are set out to promote sustainable and responsible travel in alignment with the Sustainable Developmental Goals set out by the UN.
With "think global and act local" as their motto, Offbeat Tracks uses impact based tourism as a model of employment in rural areas, thereby helping mitigate the problem of rural urban migration.
 Offbeat Tracks aims to showcase to the world the immense diversity that we are blessed with within India and use impact based travel as a means to build infrastructure, generate employment and create a network of micro entrepreneurs across India.

Watch this video to learn more about Vandana's journey and how the Goldman Sachs 10,000 Women Program at NSRCEL IIMB.

Balance is what makes a good pitch. When you are pitching to a potential client, customer or investor you need to strike a balance between the business at hand and the emotion of the person you are pitching to. Why should they invest/ buy your product and why you are the best choice are the two questions you should cover even before they have a chance to ask you these questions.

Get more insights from the Shark himself, Daymond John as to what makes a good pitch. Remember to practice and perfection will definitely be on its way

#startup #entrepreneurship #pitch #founder #growth #scaleup #business #NSRCEL

In a game of chess, the queen is the most powerful piece. She is able to move in any direction. All the other pawns in the game play to protect the queen. They always have her back, and are played keeping the position and movement of the queen in mind.

This International Women's day, we at NSRCEL-IIMB would like to highlight that a woman’s position in this world is much like that of the queen piece in chess. She is irreplaceable and she has the power to do whatever she wants to do, with the support of an army of people who love, motivate and inspire her. Behind every successful woman, there is a tribe of people who support and motivate her to be the best version of herself, and that tribe is the people she meets at NSRCEL-IIMB.

Sunbird Straws is a Made-in-India innovation transforming fallen coconut leaves into biodegradable straws. Founded by Bengaluru’s Christ University professor Saji Varghese along with his former students, this eco-friendly startup is tackling plastic pollution while empowering rural women across Karnataka, Tamil Nadu and Kerala.
With tens of thousands of straws produced daily, Sunbird Straws supplies to hotels, cafes and more in India and exports to over 10 countries.
This creates a three-fold sustainable impact by reducing plastic use, preventing leaf burning, and creating livelihoods.
Sunbird Straws was also incubated at @nsrcel_iimb under the Impact Orbit Program. They helped Sunbird Straws come up with a brand strategy that is enabling them to become a global brand.
#worldenvironmentday #beatplasticpollution #sustainablestraws

When the fintech ecosystem came together - here’s what it looked like!
NSRCEL, recently hosted a closed-room event at Indian Institute of Management Bangalore (IIM Bangalore) as a part of the FinTech Centre of Excellence, an initiative by Government of Karnataka in partnership with NSRCEL that brought together 35+ fintech founders with Chief Digital Officers (CDOs), go-to-market specialists, regulatory advisors, and industry leaders.
Founders engaged in over 70+ curated 1-on-1 sessions with the experts exploring growth strategies, regulatory readiness, compliance clarity, and scaling support. 
The day wrapped up with a networking session, where founders, regulators, and industry leaders came together to exchange insights, and foster connections that drive growth and innovation.

Learn more about the FinTech Centre of Excellence here- https://nsrcel.org/fintech-centre-of-excellence/

#NSRCEL #Fintech #StartupSupport #FounderFirst #FintechInnovation #FintechClinic #StartupIndia #FintechEcosystem #FintechEvent

This week, we kicked off the 3-day bootcamp of the Healthcare Incubation Program, an initiative by the DailyRounds / Marrow in partnership with NSRCEL at Indian Institute of Management Bangalore (IIM Bangalore), welcoming the cohort 2 of healthcare innovators.

🩺 Day 1 began with opening remarks by Prof. Srivardhini K. Jha, Professor - Entrepreneurship, IIM Bangalore and Chairperson, NSRCEL and Anand Sri Ganesh, CEO, NSRCEL emphasizing how NSRCEL is enabling founders who are solving complex healthcare challenges through innovation, business acumen, and impact-driven thinking.

The day continued with a panel discussion on "Leveraging Partnerships for Accelerated Venture Growth" featuring the speakers:

Ankita Mittal, Founder & CEO, Enhanced Innovations

Suresh Ramu, Co-Founder & CEO, Cytecare Hospitals

Dr. Dr. Sanjay Sharma, Founder, FootSecure, Co-Founder, strideAIde, and Co-Founder, Yostra & Mentor, NSRCEL

Moderated by Sridhar Ramanathan, Senior VP at IKP Knowledge Park,

the conversation explored their startup journey and they unlocked the powerful partnerships and how incubators can support the early stage startups with the partnerships or connects with clinics, hospitals, and other ecosystem players.

💬 The day concluded with a closed-room networking session, bringing together mentors, industry experts, healthcare enablers, and ecosystem partners. Founders had the chance to build new relationships, discuss collaborative opportunities, and gather valuable insights from those shaping the future of healthcare innovation in India.

This was just the beginning. Stay tuned for updates!

#NSRCEL #HealthcareIncubationProgram #Healthcare #Innovations #Healthtech #Biotech #Medtech #Startups #Founders #Bootcamp

Join us for an engaging webinar on "Enabling Circular Economy Startup Ecosystem" as we explore how startups, investors, corporates, and ecosystem enablers can collectively drive the transition to a more sustainable and resource-efficient future.

📅 Date: 25th June, Wednesday

 🕓 Time: 4:00 PM – 5:00 PM

🔗 Register Now (Link is in the bio)- https://us02web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_DLjVLy11Q22ZDHpg0zaOzw

We’ll be joined by a panel featuring Ankit Todi, Chief Sustainability Officer, Mahindra Group; Sivakumar Karmegam, Country Leader for the Innovation Lab Project, Decathlon Sports India; Hari Krishnan, Director – Investments at Greenstone Capital; and Gauri Mirashi, Co-Founder of CARPE | EcoSattva, and moderated by Akshay Joshi, Senior Program Manager- Climate CoE, NSRCEL.

From circular innovations and emerging investment trends to how key stakeholders are enabling ecosystem growth, this session will offer insights and practical perspectives for anyone building or supporting sustainability-focused ventures.

You’ll also get a chance to learn more about the Circular Economy Incubation Program, an initiative by Pernod Ricard India Foundation and how it’s supporting early-stage startups working on climate-positive, low-carbon solutions.
